# Cursor Project Rules - Screenshot Genius

## Project Intent
- Keep this project local-first, deterministic, and easy to demo.
- Favor practical reliability over framework complexity.

## Code Standards
- Use small, testable functions for business logic.
- Keep side effects isolated (filesystem, shell commands, external calls).
- Add concise logs for runtime observability.
- Prefer explicit fallback behavior over throwing hard failures.

## Safety Rules
- Never add destructive filesystem operations.
- Never silently swallow errors in core screenshot flow.
- Preserve current rename format unless explicitly requested:
  - `<app-name>-<git-branch>-<ai-summary>.<ext>`

## Testing Rules
- Any behavior change to naming, filtering, or sanitization must include/adjust tests in `test/server.test.js`.
- Use Node built-in tests (`node --test`) unless a framework is explicitly requested.

## Documentation Rules
- Keep `README.md` aligned with actual runtime behavior.
- If setup or commands change, update README in the same change set.

## PR/Commit Readiness
- Before proposing commit-ready changes, run:
  - `npm test`
- If tests fail, fix or explain the failure before proceeding.
